                <div class="w-24 h-1 bg-mustard mx-auto"></div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
                <div class="p-8 border-l-4 border-mustard bg-gray-50 rounded-r-xl">
                    <div class="text-navy text-4xl font-bold mb-2">69%</div>
                    <p class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Agencies in Crisis</p>
                    <p class="text-gray-600">69% of home care agencies report that finding and keeping skilled staff is their primary existential threat.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="p-8 border-l-4 border-mustard bg-gray-50 rounded-r-xl shadow-inner">
                    <div class="text-navy text-4xl font-bold mb-2">3 Months</div>
                    <p class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">The Critical Window</p>
                    <p class="text-gray-600">Most technicians quit within 90 days. This cycle creates massive hiring and training expenses that drain your profit.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="p-8 border-l-4 border-mustard bg-gray-50 rounded-r-xl">
                    <div class="text-navy text-4xl font-bold mb-2">High Cost</div>
                    <p class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">The Training Trap</p>
                    <p class="text-gray-600">Constantly training new staff only for them to leave results in a shrinking pool of skilled labor for your market.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

